title: For Sale:  Springfield 1911 A1
postcontent: Up for sale is a piece of true Patriotism, an icon of the United States as well known as apple pie and John Wayne, a Springfield 1911 A1.This is your chance to join this club of shooters with a refined taste of firearms.Back story.I bought this 1911 from my friend who had bought two and rarely ever shot this one. It had less than 50 rounds through it at that time and I've shot less than 200 rounds of my own.He put on the night sights, changed the grip and added an adjustable trigger set to one of the cleanest breaks I've ever felt.I don't know the name of the manufacturer for the grips, I found some one time long ago though that were selling for $60. These bad boys are like holding on to a pine cone. Think back, have you ever lost your grip on a pine cone? I dare say not! These grips ensure the same confidence in your hands.I don't know the brand of trigger either, but he said he paid $100 for it. Again.... it's got a beautiful break. It's adjustable with a little set screw.I think the night sights are Meps, but can't be sure. While they're not as bright as new, you'll have no issues finding aim at a target in the dark.There are 2 Wilson Combat 8 round magazines included, 1 8 round Cobra and the original 7 rounder. I rotate my mags every 2 weeks to keep the springs fresh. It's almost a ritual.The holster is an awesome CompTac MTAC right handed and it comes with both C clips and the standard clips.Make sure you have a good strong carry belt and you'll have no issues tucking around this guy. I wore it this one time for a business meeting with a suite and no coat and had no issues for a solid 8 hours. Of course, if I went to use the bathroom I'd just retuck. I've worn it plenty at other more casual settings and never had an issue. Just read the reviews on this holster.This holster is $80 + S&H plus the extra for the other clips.There's just something about carrying a full size .45 that gives you a boldness. It's not hubris, but rather the assurance of your ancestors, knowing that they too trusted their lives to such a fine piece of workmanship and certainly won many of victories with it at their side.So, brass tacks. Why am I selling it?Honestly, I don't really want to. I'm not strapped for cash, it isn't buyers remorse, wifey isn't making me.  It's just that someday soon I hope to start a trust, maybe get some cans, etc, and this gun just won't accommodate that. I thought if I could get close to what I have in it, I could get the Sig I want to put a can on and have some left over for the family lawyer to start the paperwork.And I don't really shoot it enough. A machine such as this deserves to be used, loved and appreciated!How much? $1,000. Prettttty firm unless you're trading a full size Sig in .45.Base gun is $750 + taxes.Trigger, $100Night sights, $100Grips, $602 Wilson mags are $80, Cobra is $30MTAC is $100 shipped with extra clipsFobus single mag holster, $30That's $1,250.-17% for 'used,' I think it's fair.I'm happy to meet just about anywhere in public in the daytime within 15 miles of 30046 and 30680 after 6pm. I prefer to see a CWP on purchase to make sure you're not a felon.We live in a scary and sinful world were there are a lot of cheats and thieves trying to steal from everyone and a certain level of lowness surrounds those who buy and sell firearms. If you don't bring personal protection to a cash transaction of $1,000, you have more faith in humanity than I do. I say that so you know I won't be alarmed if you come with caution. Just know I will too.Let me know if you have serious inquiries and I'll do everything to help!
